Hot Fudge Pudding Cake Ingredients:

1-1/4 cups granulated sugar, divided
1 cup all-purpose flour
1/2 cup HERSHEY'S Cocoa, divided
2 teaspoons baking powder
1/4 teaspoon salt
1/2 cup milk
1/3 cup butter or margarine, melted
1-1/2 teaspoons vanilla extract
1/2 cup packed light brown sugar
1-1/4 cups hot water
Whipped topping

Directions:
    1. Heat oven to 350Â°F. Combine 3/4 cup granulated sugar, flour, 1/4 cup cocoa, baking powder and salt.
        Stir in milk, butter and vanilla; beat until smooth.
    2. Pour batter into ungreased 9-inch square baking pan. Stir together remaining 1/2 cup granulated sugar,
        brown sugar and remaining 1/4 cup cocoa; sprinkle mixture evenly over batter. Pour hot water over top; do not stir.
    3. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Remove from oven; let stand 15 minutes. Serve in dessert dishes,
        spooning sauce from bottom of pan over top. Garnish with whipped topping.

